# ============================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================
# This .gitignore is configured for a school asset management system
# with sensitive data handling requirements.
#
# CRITICAL FILES TO NEVER COMMIT:
# - .env (contains database passwords, API keys)
# - public/signatures/* (user signature images)
# - public/uploads/* (uploaded documents/photos)
# - credentials.json, token.json (OAuth tokens)
# - *.dump, *.backup.sql (database backups)
#
# If you accidentally commit sensitive files:
# 1. Remove from Git: git rm --cached <file>
# 2. Add to .gitignore
# 3. Commit the change
# 4. For already-pushed commits, consider: git filter-branch or BFG Repo-Cleaner
# 5. Rotate any exposed credentials immediately
#
# For more info: https://git-scm.com/docs/gitignore
